text: Tahar Chaïbi (17 February 1946 – 29 April 2014) was a Tunisian footballer. He played as a midfielder for Club Africain and the national team. He was born in Tunis, Tunisia. Chaïbi died from complications from a stroke, aged 68. ==References== Category:1946 births Category:2014 deaths Category:Deaths from stroke Category:Tunisian footballers Category:Sportspeople from Tunis
